name: media_png_valid_idat_one_byte_chunks
description: |
  A valid 1x1 RGBA PNG whose zlib stream is split into eleven consecutive IDAT
  chunks, each carrying one byte. This is a deliberately awkward but conforming
  streaming layout: the decoder must concatenate consecutive IDAT data before
  inflating it. It catches implementations that try to inflate each IDAT chunk
  independently or accidentally reset decompression state at chunk boundaries.

  This file is independently constructed for this corpus and is MIT licensed.
  The PNG Suite includes a related "all IDAT chunks length one" class, and the
  PNG specification defines IDAT chunking:
  https://www.libpng.org/pub/png/pngsuite.html
  https://www.w3.org/TR/png-3/#11IDAT
format: hex
decode-as: bytes
mime-type: image/png
licence: MIT
pair:
  - with: valid-minimal-rgba-1x1.input
    hint: tricky
tags:
  - "media"
  - "image"
  - "png"
  - "valid-png"
  - "idat"
  - "chunk-boundary"
  - "streaming"
---
